  						<table width=75% border=0 cellpadding=5 cellspacing=0 align=center>  <tr>
    <td width='100%' align='left' valign='top' bgcolor='#0E024D' colspan=5 class='spti2'>MAGICIAN FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db2' colspan=2>Click <a href=faq.asp?Action=SubmitQ>Here</a> To Submit A Frequently Asked Question<hr size='1'></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>When do Magician Pets get duel wield?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>Pets summoned after Level 20 have the ability to dual wield. This will increase the number of attacks which they can do each round.<P>
In order to activate this ability you must give the pet two weapons, these can be summoned or normal, but must be one hand items, and not restricted to a specific slot.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>Does giving my pet a weapon make him attack faster or do I just have to give him weapons to get him to dual wield?
</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>You must give your pet two weapons in order for it to dual wield.  They can be summoned weapons, and they do not have to be two different weapons.<P>
This will not increase the attack rate of your pet, but will allow it to attack more frequently because it is using two hands instead of just one.<P>
To increase the actual attack rate of the pet you should use a Burnout spell.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>How much damage do my Water and Fire pets do with their Direct Damage spells?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>The actual damage done by your pets increases with each level.<P>
Water Elemental attacks can do between 2 and 61 damage as they increase in level.  The highest level water elementals can do up to 140 damage when used with a Staff of Mastery.<P>
Fire Elementals can do between 2 and 61 damage also with their attacks, but also get the added bonus of a damage shield which can inflict between 3 and 62 damage every time it is hit.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>What is a focus item and what's it used for?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>Focus items are used to enhance a Magicians powers.  There are two types of these: Lesser Focus Items, and the Staves of Mastery.<P>
Both of these have the same effect: they increase the natural powers of your summoned pet.  They also make your pets larger at higher levels.<P>
Lesser Focus Items can be found through completing quests in the Temple of Solusek Ro.  The Staffs of Mastery are found on the more powerful monsters in the game.  Phinigel Autropus has the Staff of Water Mastery, Innoruuk the Prince of Hate has the Earth Mastery staff.  The Air staff is believed to be a quest in the Plane of Sky, and the Fire Staff is believed to be in Veeshans Peak.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>I've heard that Water elementals are immune to poison. Is this true & are they the only ones? Also do any of the other pets have special immunities & what are they if so?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>Actually no pet is totally immune to any particular spell type.  Pets do have quite good resistance levels though, and generally a fast hitpoint recovery, which means DoT's rarely kill them.  You can of course increase their protection by having your pet buffed by somone.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>I have heard that pets benefit most from high damage (such as 2-handed) weapons until duel-wield capable, then high delay (1-handed) weapons become more important. Is this true, & if not, what are the key factors in weapon selection for pets?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>Before the patch which gave Magician pets dual wield, the delay of a weapon <u>did</u> make a difference.  However when this patch went in the speed of weapons was removed, and now it does not matter at all what weapon you give your pet as long as it is a one-handed weapon which can be equipped in either slot.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>How much Experience does my pet take when I do more than 50% of the damage to the mob?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>If you do the majority of the damage when fighting with your pet it will not take any experience from the monster.  This applies only to soling however, and will not impact upon grouped situations.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>How much Experience does my pet take when I do less than 50% of the damage to the mob?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>If your pet does more than 50% of the damage required to kill the mob it will take half the experience of the mob.  This applies only to soling however, and will not impact upon grouped situations.<P>Having an Enchanter or Cleric do a mem blur towards the end of the fight and then nuking hard will normally get you full experience.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>Does the type of pet determine how much experience is taken in a kill?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>The type of pet chosen has no direct influence on how much experienced is derived from each kill.  However, different pets have different damage outputs, and mobs such as water or air pets can do large damage quickly, easily doing over 50% of the overall damage which does reduce the experience obtained from killing the mob.<P>The damage shield on the pet (natural or mage cast) will not count as part of the pets overall damage.
</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>What are some quest-only spells for Magicians?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>The only magician spells which need to be obtained via quest are those for Level 50+ which are received through swapping spells.  You can find more info on these in our spell list <a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/spells/spells.asp?Class=Magician'><b>here</b></a>.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>When I go to ask for a group, normally most groups will pick a tank, over a Magician of the same level. Even though the Magician/pet combo is much more effective in Combat, why to most group prefer Melee Classes over a Superior Caster/Pet class?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>This is probably due to the fact that pets often disobey there masters and run off, and also because pets can take exp if they do more than 50% of the damage.  If you spend enough time with a good group or guild they will generally learn to appreciate your role.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>Where can I find malachite?
</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>You can purchace Malachite, and any other magician summoning component, at a gem vendor found in mostly every city. You can also find these gems off of creatures.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>After lvl 50, what does each type of pet become (which class is it based off of)?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>The earth pet is modeled after the warrior, fire from the wizard, air was created to be like the monk and water is fashioned after the rogue. </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>At what lvl is a good time to start the quests for Stein of Ulysis, Shovel of Ponz, Torch of Alna, and Broom of Tkilon?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>The focus object quests should best be done from level 29 onwards.  They do not work on pets less than level 29, and ideally by around level 34 you will be well equipped to obtain the items.<P>
Many of the dungeon areas where you will be fighting during these levels will have parts of these quests, so with some good planning it will not be too difficult to complete them all by level 34.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='db' width=15><b>Q:</b></td><td class='db2' valign='top'>You said giving a pet a weapon will not increase attack rate, how about damage?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign='top' class='dbti' width=15><b>A:</b></td><td class='db' valign='top'>The weapon given to a pet does affect it's damage output. A higher delay/damage ratio will create more damage than one of a lower ratio.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan=2>&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db' colspan=2 align=right><a class='db2'href=faq.asp?Action=Show&Class=Magician&Page=2><b>Next Page</b></a></td>
  </tr>
</table>

  						<!--#endContent#-->
			</center></td>
